Diagnosis.
Body (except head) black (
Fig. 9
); head transverse and reddish-yellow; eye in dorsal view 1.5 × longer than temple (
Fig. 10H
); eye in lateral view 0.9 × higher than wide; frons largely smooth, rugulose near antennal sockets and densely punctate laterally (
Fig. 10H
); vertex and temple smooth (
Fig. 10H
); face rather convex medially, densely and coarsely rugose-reticulate with transverse striation (

Fig. 
10I

); clypeus subtriangular, protruding forward, densely and finely reticulate-punctate (

Fig. 
10I

); mandible rugose and with 4 teeth or lobes (
Fig. 10J
); notauli crenulated and incomplete, impressed on disc; mesoscutum smooth and with sparse setae anteriorly; medio-posterior depression short, densely crenulated (
Fig. 10B
); precoxal sulcus crenuate; metapleuron with dense punctures (
Fig. 10C
); surface of propodeum reticulate-rugose and areola absent (
Fig. 10D
); pterostigma 5.4 × longer than its maximum width (
Fig. 10A
); hind coxa finely punctate (
Fig. 10B
); metasoma longitudinally striate and some reticulate-rugosity between striae, length of first tergite 0.85 × its apical width (
Fig. 10E
), setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.6 × as long as fore wing (total visible sheath 0.7 ×), and 1.5 × as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 10G
).

Head. Transverse (
Fig. 10H
), width of head 1.6 × its lateral length (
Fig. 10H
), and 1.5 × wider than mesoscutum; antenna with 46 segments, third segment (including annellus) 0.7 × as long as fourth segment, length of third and fourth segments 1.7 and 3.3 × their width, respectively (
Fig. 10F
); length of maxillary palp twice height of head; eye in dorsal view 1.5 × as long as temple (
Fig. 10H
); eye in lateral view 0.9 × higher than wide (

Fig. 
10I

); frons mainly smooth; vertex and temple smooth (
Fig. 10H
); OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL= 14:5:4; face twice wider than high, rather convex medially, densely and coarsely rugose-reticulate with transverse striae (

Fig. 
10I

); clypeus small, subtriangular, protruding forward, densely and finely reticulate-punctate (

Fig. 
10I

); malar space absent; mandible with 4 teeth or lobes, enlarged apically, dorsal tooth enlarged, lobe-shaped (
Fig. 10K
), ventral tooth medium-sized and lobe-shaped, ventral carina protruding, middle tooth curved (
Fig. 10L
), medial length of mandible 1.6 × its maximum width (
Fig. 10L
).

