subSubSection.paragraph:
Mesosoma. Length of mesosoma 1.5 × its height (
Fig. 10C
); pronope round, wide and deep; medio-anteriorly pronotum distinctly crenulate, remainder of pronotum smooth (
Fig. 10C
); epicnemial area rugose with some crenulae; precoxal sulcus long, widely crenulate, not reaching middle coxa; pleural sulcus crenulated ventrally; episternal scrobe round and deep; metapleuron smooth medially, but reticulate-rugose ventrally (
Fig. 10C
); notauli crenulated and incomplete, anteriorly impressed on disc (
Fig. 10B
); medio-posterior depression comparatively short, not extended to middle of mesoscutum, scutellar sulcus deep, with one longitudinal carina and two short carina, sulcus 3.0 × wider than its maximum length; scutellum smooth and triangular (
Fig. 10B
); surface of propodeum densely and coarsely reticulate-rugose, areola present but inconspicuous posteriorly (
Fig. 10D
).

Wings (
Fig. 10A
). Pterostigma wide, 4.2 × as long as maximum width r:3-SR:SR1 = 5:12:49; 1-SR+M slightly sinuate; SR1 straight; r 0.7 × as long as the width of pterostigma; cu-a interstitial; 3-CU1 as long as CU1b; 2-SR:3- SR:r-m = 20:15:13; m-cu postfurcal, slightly sinuate and almost parallel to 1-M; first subdiscal cell 3.8 × as long as wide; M+CU1 unsclerotized basally. Hind wing: M+CU: 1-M: 1r-m = 25:15:6; m-cu far antefurcal.

Legs. Hind coxa smooth, without ventro-basal tubercle; tarsal claws moderately robust, longer than arolium (
Fig. 10G
); length of femur, tibia and basitarsus of hind leg 4.4, 8.3 and 6.7 × their width, respectively; apical appendages of hind tarsal segments absent, segments ventrally densely bristly setose (( 
Fig. 10G
).

Colour. Dark reddish brown (
Fig. 9
); 6 basal segments of antenna, mandible, face, clypeus, legs except hind tibia and hind tarsus yellowish; head and first and second tergite of metasoma brownish yellow; third tergite of metasoma, hind tibia and tarsus dark brown; metasoma dark reddish brown; pterostigma and veins brown; wing membrane slightly infuscated.
